    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-09-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-09-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="348"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d348">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.6231/404</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Special Adviser to the President on Foreign Trade</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Peek</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Under Secretary of State</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-09-06">September 6,
                            1934</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Phillips</hi>: Some weeks ago Mr. James D. Mooney,
                    President of General Motors Export Company, and I discussed with you the
                    possibilities of an exchange of certain of our products for certain German
                    products. The purpose of this note is to advise you that these negotiations have
                    been resumed, and you will probably hear of them through the German Embassy
                    within the next few days.</p>
                <p>I shall be glad to discuss with you any details and keep you fully informed.</p>
                <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">George N. Peek</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
